	<p>
		<div>Aalto PRO, together with various cooperation partners, organized a two week Sustainable Communities workshop in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania, in March 2013. The workshop “Managing Urban Futures” rounded up 27 urban professionals from East Africa and South East Asia to learn about the current practices and thinking regarding cities and sustainable urban development. The course provided practical examples and methods on how to use city planning as a tool for sustainable development and thus decrease the rapid and uncontrolled urbanization, which is one of the biggest development problems in the World.</div><div><br></div><div>The workshop had an emphasis on finding tools for supporting sustainability in urban planning by focusing on the topics of citizen participation and empowerment, sustainable urban infrastructure, housing and environmental management. The participants included representatives from academics, NGOs, local authorities and central government agencies.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Aalto PRO organized the workshop together with UONGOZI Institute, UN-HABITAT, UNEP, Asian Institute of Technology, and University of Nairobi. The panel discussion was moderated by Åsa Jonsson from UN-HABITAT, and the guest speakers included the Ambassador Sinikka Antila from the Embassy of Finland and Dr Camilius Lekule from ARDHI University.</div><div><br></div><div>The Sustainable Communities course was held for the fifth time and has previously been organized in Helsinki (2007), Bangkok (2008 and 2012), and Nairobi (2009). This year, the workshop was coordinated by the UONGOZI Institute of African Leadership for Sustainable Development. The course is partly funded by the Government of Finland, and contributes to the implementation of Aalto University’s strategic plan to strengthen education for sustainable development. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>For more information:</div><div><a href="http://aaltopro.aalto.fi" title="" target="_blank">aaltopro.aalto.fi</a></div><div><a href="http://www.aaltopro.fi/sustainable_communities" title="" target="_blank">www.aaltopro.fi/sustainable_communities</a></div><div>terhi.wermundsen(a)aalto.fi or matleena.muhonen(a)aalto.fi</div><div><br></div><div>Photo copyright Matleena Muhonen 2013.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>
